SIMPLE: scandalous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scandalous
<hw>Scan"dal*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>scandaleux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Giving offense to the
conscience or moral feelings; exciting reprobation; calling out
condemnation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nothing <qex>scandalous</qex> or offensive unto any.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disgraceful to reputation; bringing shame or infamy;
opprobrious; <as>as, a <ex>scandalous</ex> crime or vice</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Defamatory; libelous; <as>as, a <ex>scandalous</ex>
story</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scandalously</ent>⟦br⟧
